caption: Had take out - Drunken noodles were very flavorful and delicious, however the Thai fried was was ordinary and wasn't anything to write home about.
Really good thai food.  The menu is a bit small and I think they could expand it a bit but everything I've ordered here I've really enjoyed.
Friendly staff. Food is good.
Food was excellent and the service as well and the restaurant is nice and cozy

Food is not good. Ordered 2 items and it was gross. Food was cold. Taste was so far away from a Thai Food. I’m sad because my husband based it on the reviews sadly food here was not good at all. Soggy noodles. Spices not great.

I've ordered several times from this place and they deliver fast and food is nice and hot (temperature wise). They forgot to include shrimp in my fried rice once and they replaced it immediately and without asking for the wrong one back. Now that's amazing customer service!
The Tom Ka soup is PEEEERRRRRFECT  thank god for this <3
This place always delivers. They serve awesome food for affordable pricing, there no long wait even when the place is loaded.
Delicious and great prices!
Great food and service
Great food and service

Food was absolutely delicious. Incredibly flavorful and not greasy. Particularly enjoyed the fish cakes, roti prata, thai dumplings, and the tom yum fried rice. If you like spice and tell them to make it legitimately spicy, they will deliver!
Me and my husband loved ... very tasty food and excellent service

This place serves delicious and authentic Thai food, with warm, friendly, and hospitable service.  The fried whole snapper (Pla Pree Wan) was cooked in a skillful way where the outside was crispy while maintaining a soft and moist flesh inside.  We ordered two noodles, Pad Kee Mao and Pad Wun See, which were both flavorful and contained fresh vegetables.  A gem on the block, give it a try yourself!
Awesome spot to buy some food when in a hurry. The service is rapid, prices are convenient, awesome vibes. Will visit here again
Fantastic, must eat here!  Basil sauce was amazing and the service was great!
Very neat and welcoming spot. They offer big meals and for affordable rates. We liked the meals very much and the staff were super attentive and chatty. Highly recommended.
This place simply knows how to treat their clients. Regularly with a very kind approach. The food is conveniently priced, regularly tasty and neat.

This spot is the one I like best. I go to many restaurants but to this restaurant I  constantly return again and again. The crew is very amicable and the cooking they offer is so flavorful. I would always prefer to have a decent meal in this place. I highly recommend this place.
Delicious pad see ew! Haven’t tried other dishes yet but definitely will order again.
LOVE Mee Thai. Fantastic food and lovely people.
Small portion wrong order!!! Not worth of money 👎🏻👎🏻👎🏻👎🏻👎🏻👎🏻👎🏻👎🏻👎🏻👎🏻👎🏻👎🏻 !!!!! Never again!!!
Good food.

This was my second time visiting this place. I highly recommend them. Authentic Thai Cuisine and great customer service. Patty or (Pattie) not sure how to spell her name, was extremely nice and welcomed me with such warmth and happiness. I had the Tom Yum soup which was “Ahhh-Ma-Zing! The mushrooms and shrimps were perfectly cooked and that sauce had the right amount of lime in there. I can still taste it. The Pad Kee Mao was delicious as well, filled with flavor and very spicy just the way I like it. I will come back and you guys should try them out too!
Great thai food friendly atmosphere and service
Delicious tamarind duck and spring rolls. Service was very pleasant and fast.
One of the best Thai Food in Brooklyn!!! Great service too! & Thank You Mee Thai Cuisine, I enjoyed my food.
Top notch. Got the green curry and the flavor was vibrant and authentic. Solid spicy level too. One of the best I've tried in the city.
I can call us discerning because we ordered the same dishes we always order in every Thai restaurant. And everything was so good. They know their craft.
Good Thai food and service!
I’ve had the papaya salad, green curry and pad Thai.  All were really delicious.  Such friendly staff as well!
This spot constantly delivers. They serve fantastic food for fair prices, there is no waiting time even when the place is loaded.
Waiter was very welcoming and attentive. The food was flavorful and yummy. Cute little spot!

When I first came here with my dear friend, we were the only ones and it was (tbh) a little awkward. But the hospitality was very good and the waiter was soooo nice. So I went like,” This is the one.” Then we order food. To be honest the Papaya salad was not lacking in flavor at all. It was delicious! The savory flavor made you want to eat more. The best part has to be the Pad Thai. The flavor is sooo good. Perfect sauce combo,

Such friendly service. Very nice quaint place. Music is nice and low, so are the lights. Lunch specials are the standard Thai menu items. I had a clear soup and pineapple fried rice. The food was so vibrant. There was plenty of various veg in all menu options. It just tasted like the food was made with love and care.
Food is okay but not the usual thai
Food is excellent.  Enjoyed the pineapple fried rice.
Excelente service and great tasting food! Highly recommend this place!
Great place. Tasty Thai food. Wonderful lunch specials. Service is friendly, I love it here. I have brought both my mother and my mother in law the first week we moved here!

Real relaxing and inexpensive Thai restaurant that is friendly and tasty 😋 . Little to no wait time and the food is made to perfection. Would definitely recommend for a night out with the family our a. Relaxing night with a love one. The chicken wings are to die for 😋🤤

Cozy Thai restaurant that is child friendly.   Took my kids there for Friday night outing.  We all enjoyed our meal and were out within 1 hour of sitting.  No wait to get seated.  Would definitely return.  Spent $55 for 3 meals, 1 appetitizer, no drinks, tip included.
I order take out from here regularly and have dined in as well. In addition to the great lunch specials, I also order Thai ice tea and crispy chicken wings. Wonderful staff.

Just ate here. Currently still sitting in the restaurant waiting to pay and it's amazing. The food tastes great and is reasonably priced. Definitely happy my family and I dropped in. Jessie, our waiter, is amazing. He recommended the thai iced tea with lychee and it's amazing! If you're ever here, ask for him! He is super attentive
Loved, loved their Thai chicken fried rice.  Good service, good price, but great fried rice. Haven't gotten better since leaving Brooklyn.

The papaya salad was so refreshing on my palate while putting a bit of burn on my tongue. The wide Drunken Noodles were soft and coated in the sauce, the shrimp plump and flavorful accompanied by stir fried veggies. To top it off they have very friendly service.
Food is very good!
Really authentic Thai cuisine and it is very affordable. Would go back there again.
Cozy atmosphere, staffs are really nice. I ordered fried noodles it was delicious !
Excellent food and service
Ok not great.
Great food for great price. Not a fancy place but comfortable and nice staffs.
I order from this place every week. The pinapple fried rice lunch special and Thai bubble tea are amaz!
This place is a gem: Great Thai food, courteous service, reasonable prices.
Thank you Miss Pam from Thailand 🇹🇭, I felt happy to know this restaurant, and it looks good. If a restaurant operates by nice workers. It deserves to have good business—from Julian a art promoter

My favorite Thai restaurant in the area. It tasts as good as in Thailand and if you tell them to make it Thai spicy, they will! Papaya salad and all curry/chilli dishes are just amazing. Cooked with love!

small neighborhood restaurant that has a nice selection of authentic Thai food. I interviewed the waiter but he just said 'yes' to everything. He claimed there was a ramp to cover the small step at entrance for wheelchairs. There is a small hallway to get to the restrooms which can fit a wheel chair. The food was good- I had lychee Ice tea- lots of flavor that I added 2 cups of water and it still had flavor. Next I tried the fried tofu which was not full of oil or crispy crunchy. I just found it odd as I paid the bill of under $10/ I gave $20 and the waiter asked if I wanted my change.  Street parking only
Delicious and great service. Had the pad ke mao and it was fantastic.
Great chicken peanut
Their beef salad is pretty great along with their fried ice-cream.

This was my second time here. The service, staff and food are all great!!! Additionally, it's not expensive. The first time I went here was on a date and this time around I went hanging out with an old high school friend of mine. So, it's a versatile restaurant able to accommodate whatever vibe you're working with. This time around I got steak and flat noodles (as opposed to the stringy variety). Very flavorful and a little kick from the spiciness. My friend enjoyed his food as well. I don't know when, but I do know that I'll be back here.
Best Pad-Si Ew in Brooklyn I've ever tasted
This is my favorite Thai spot. I am a regular there. Food is ALWAYS good!
Fresh, delicious food - especially the Panang Curry. The only reason for less than 5 stars is that the portions are significantly smaller than expected.
Always very tasty, great lunch specials.  I especially like the curries with rice and vegetarian duck. Nice staff too.
The staff is awesome. The food is done well. A very good place to eat.

I was a little concerner when I went in and was the ONLY customer. But they had my favorite coconut curry dish and it was good. I've had too many bad ones that all I can say was I was happy they did not disappoint. I would go again
Fast service, tasty food. good for groups.
Great food and quick service!
Great food, kind staff, pleasant atmosphere – what's not to love?
I love the curry puffs.
decent food and prices. curry puffs were great.
Cute no-frills thai place. The beef noodle soup was plentiful and delicious.
My favorite restaurant
Amazing food for super cheap prices. Food came amazingly quick. Good service and location. 👌👌

(Translated by Google) Fantastic Thai food with a cheap special lunch and generous portions. Highly recommended  (Original) Fantástica comida tailandesa con un lunch special barato y de raciones generosas. Muy recomendable
I come here every week. The food is delicious and the staff is so nice !! You gotta have the calamari. Its delicious
Nice cozy place for a quick bite
Awesome food, very authentic

My favorite Thai place in Park Slope.  Their food is very tasty and the portions are very big.  Delivery is super quick (often 15-20 minutes after you order) and the food is always piping hot.  It's slightly more expensive than other Thai places in the neighborhood, but very much worth it.  It's never that crowded inside, and offers a quiet place to enjoy a meal.
Healthy fresh yummy!
